    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "1939\nTHE LARGEST AND LAST OF PAA'S FLYING BOATS WAS THE BOEING 314. THIS\nCLIPPER INAUGURATED THE FIRST TRANSATLANTIC SERVICE IN 1939. THE PLANE\nCARRIED 56 PASSENGERS BY\n106-FEET WITH A WINGSPREAD OF 152-FEET. THE 314 CLIPPER HAD A RANGE OF\n2,000 MILES POWERED BY FOUR 1600-HORSEPOWER WRIGHT CYCLONE ENGINES WITH\nA CRUISING SPEED OF 184-MILES-PER-HOUR. THE 314 WAS ALSO THE MOST\nLUXURIOUS PLANE PAA EVER OPERATED. IT HAD SIX PASSENGER COMPARTMENTS,\nLOUNGE, AND BRIDAL SUITE. A TOTAL OF 12 B-314s WERE BUILT."
